President Obama has announced his intent to appoint three individuals to key administration posts. Dr. Maria Lombardo will be appointed as the Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Christopher Columbus Fellowship Foundation. She has experience in education and has been recognized for her work in cultural education programs. William Sisk will be appointed as a member of the Committee for Purchase from People Who are Blind or Severely Disabled. He has over 20 years of experience with the General Services Administration and currently serves as the Assistant Commissioner in the Office of General Supplies and Services. Steven L. VanRoekel will be appointed as the Federal Chief Information Officer and Administrator of the Office of Electronic Government in the Office of Management and Budget. He has experience in technology and previously served as the Executive Director of Citizen and Organizational Engagement at the United States Agency for International Development.